      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot (with a matching lid) with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1632303401532-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1632303401532-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1632303401532-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1632303401532-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1632303401532-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>meat-free mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) and cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Tip: Try not to stir too often so the mince gets nice and brown!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632303414235-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632303414235-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632303414235-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632303414235-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632303414235-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the meat-free mince is browning, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>,<strong> chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and your <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>chipotle stock</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632303428663-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632303428663-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632303428663-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632303428663-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632303428663-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the meat-free mince has browned, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>,<strong> ground smoked paprika</strong> and<strong> ground cumin</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632303455367-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632303455367-x400.jpg",
